From b024d77533cebdf1740ccf74d2f946ac39452e69 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 23:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm: airoha: an7563-evb: enable Airoha BMT on the SPI-NAND
 node

Turn the Airoha BMT plug-in introduced in
600-mtd-spi-nand-add-airoha-bmt-support.patch on for the AN7563 EVB:

  - Set CONFIG_MTD_NAND_AIROHA_BMT=y in configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
    so airoha_bmt.o is built into the U-Boot binary.
  - Add the `airoha,bmt;` boolean to &spi_nand in
    arch/arm/dts/an7563-evb.dts so airoha_bmt_attach() recognises
    the device during spinand_probe() and hooks the dual BBT/BMT
    layer in.

Without this opt-in pair the SPI-NAND device is exposed raw and the
ATF / preloader-managed bad-block tables are ignored in U-Boot,
causing visible-MTD size mismatch with the kernel and unmapped
remap entries when erase / write triggers a bad block at runtime.
Other Airoha boards (AN7581 / AN7583 / EN7523) keep AIROHA_BMT off
until they explicitly opt in the same way.

The Linux side enables the same property on
target/linux/airoha/dts/an7563-evb.dts together with
CONFIG_MTD_NAND_MTK_BMT=y in the AN7563 kernel target config so
both stages walk the same on-flash layout.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm/dts/an7563-evb.dts    | 2 ++
 configs/an7563_evb_defconfig   | 1 +
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
+++ b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
@@ -51,6 +51,7 @@ CONFIG_LED_GPIO=y
 CONFIG_MTD=y
 CONFIG_DM_MTD=y
 CONFIG_MTD_SPI_NAND=y
+CONFIG_MTD_NAND_AIROHA_BMT=y
 CONFIG_AIROHA_ETH=y
 CONFIG_DM_MDIO=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MII=y
--- a/arch/arm/dts/an7563-evb.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/dts/an7563-evb.dts
@@ -47,6 +47,8 @@
 };
 
 &spi_nand {
+	airoha,bmt;
+
 	partitions {
 		compatible = "fixed-partitions";
 		#address-cells = <1>;
